  "prompt": "How much do furniture salesmen make?",
  "response": "The earnings of furniture salesmen can vary widely based on factors such as location, experience, the specific store or company they work for, and their sales performance. Generally, furniture salespeople may earn a combination of a base salary and commissions on sales.\n\n1. **Base Salary**: Many furniture salesmen earn a base salary that can range from $25,000 to $50,000 per year, depending on the region and the store's policies.\n\n2. **Commissions**: In addition to their base salary, sales commissions can significantly boost earnings. Commissions might range from 5% to 10% of sales, but this can vary. High-performing salespeople in busy stores can make additional income that can bring their total earnings (salary plus commissions) to anywhere from $40,000 to over $100,000 per year.\n\n3. **Bonuses and Incentives**: Some companies offer bonuses or incentives for meeting sales targets, which can further increase total earnings.\n\n4. **Experience and Location**: More experienced salespeople or those working in higher-end furniture stores might earn more than those in entry-level positions or lower-tier stores. Additionally, salespeople in urban areas or regions with a higher cost of living may earn more than those in rural areas.\n\nOverall, while entry-level positions may offer lower salaries, there is potential for significant earnings for successful salespeople in the furniture industry.",
